cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper presents a deep-learning framework for real-time multiple spatio-temporal action localisation, classification and early prediction. The use of convolutional neural networks and online algorithms suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on achieving state-of-the-art results also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of videos and action detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of real-time detection and prediction suggests that the paper may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
